                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>At the entrance (left side) into the Varadarāja-Perumāḷ shrine in the Chandramauḷīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Year 24.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription in Tamil verse is dated in the year 24 of the reign of an unnamed king. Palaeographically it may be assigned to the 11th century.</p>						
                            
                            <p>It records the construction of a door to the temple of Vishṇu (<hi rend="italic">Māl</hi>) at Vakkarai by Kaṇḍaṉ Turuvvaikon of Maḍandai (?). </p>						
                            
                        </summary>
